         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1958"/><citedRange>300</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... Some, as enemies, withheld, as it were, friendship from each other [and] said: Don’t do [it, my] son! The others (?) ... </seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a1 #a2 #a3 #a4 #a5 #a6 #a7 #a8 #b1 #b2 #b3 #b4 #b5 #b6 #b7 #b8"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:sieg1952"/><citedRange>31</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... 1. (Like) the extinguished [has tried to] go to the extinction, just so everyone should try ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>181</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... penetrated [and] (surrounded) on the right side by the ray. 2. (In) such a way ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (Into the hot hells cold) rays they released; into the cold hells they released hot rays ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>303</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [inhabitants of] hell, animals [and] pretas were beaten by thirst and hunger. With them ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (|| In the N.-)tune: || But this Saṃsāra is very faulty, although exceedingly lustrous ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a7"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the earth with mountains [and] trees ... as it were. On the earth and in the air space ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a8"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the hells. They were ... as the abode [of gods] ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... surrounded (by) the ray ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>101f</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>54</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1972"/><citedRange>455</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... like the heavenly earth ... (musical instruments) roared, they made resound as it were ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>54</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... in the hells the hell-guardians stood first, black like mountains ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>54</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... with hands put together the hell-guardians despondently looked at the Buddhas. Hate [and] discord ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1966"/><citedRange>267</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1997"/><citedRange>91</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1997"/><citedRange>92</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... ([inhabitants of] hell), animals and pretas, all forgot their sufferings. Gods [and] humans, too, set (?) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1969"/><citedRange>259</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the earth-god shook, ... (heavenly) flowers (were raining down and) lovely (wreaths. 5.) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b7"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... created the marvel. (There)fore excessive [and] countless beings ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b8"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... For redemption they sowed the healing roots. Having seen this matter ...</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... zur Erlösung säten sie die Heilswurzeln.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">... for redemption they sowed the roots of healing.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>438</citedRange></bibl