               <item n="m_translation_old">a1 ... Some, as enemies, withheld, as it were, friendship from each other [and] said: Don’t do [it, my] son! The others (?) ... 
a2 ... 1. (Like) the extinguished [has tried to] go to the extinction, just so everyone should try ...
a3 ... penetrated [and] (surrounded) on the right side by the ray. 2. (In) such a way ...
a4 ... (Into the hot hells cold) rays they released; into the cold hells they released hot rays ...
a5 ... [inhabitants of] hell, animals [and] pretas were beaten by thirst and hunger. With them ...
a6 ... (|| In the N.-)tune: || But this Saṃsāra is very faulty, although exceedingly lustrous ...
a7 ... the earth with mountains [and] trees ... as it were. On the earth and in the air space ...
a8 ... the hells. They were ... as the abode [of gods] ...
b1 ... surrounded (by) the ray ...
b2 ... like the heavenly earth ... (musical instruments) roared, they made resound as it were ...
b3 ... in the hells the hell-guardians stood first, black like mountains ...
b4 ... with hands put together the hell-guardians despondently looked at the Buddhas. Hate [and] discord ...
b5 ... ([inhabitants of] hell), animals and pretas, all forgot their sufferings. Gods [and] humans, too, set (?) ...
b6 ... the earth-god shook, ... (heavenly) flowers (were raining down and) lovely (wreaths. 5.) ...
b7 ... created the marvel. (There)fore excessive [and] countless beings ...
b8 ... For redemption they sowed the healing roots. Having seen this matter ...</item>
